3,I had a terrible day at work. Can you help me feel better?,baseline,"Of course, I'd be happy to help! Sorry to hear that you had a terrible day at work. It can be really tough when things don't go as planned, and it can be even harder when it affects our mood and well-being.

First of all, let me offer you a virtual hug. Sometimes, all we need is someone to listen and offer a bit of comfort. Would you like to talk about what happened at work that made your day so difficult? Sometimes sharing our struggles with someone who cares can help us feel better and gain a new perspective.

If you're not ready to talk about it yet, that's totally okay. Sometimes we need some time and space to process our emotions before we're ready to share. In that case, let me offer you some relaxation techniques that might help you unwind and feel better. Would you like to try some deep breathing exercises, or maybe listen to some calming music together?

Remember that it's okay to have bad days sometimes, and it's important to be kind to ourselves as we navigate through them. You're not alone, and I'm here to support you in any way I can. What do you say? Would you like to talk about your day, or would you prefer to focus on relaxation techniques?",220,4,9,0.04090909090909091,6,0.02727272727272727,7,0.031818181818181815,0,0.0,0,0.0,0,0.0,22,0.1,9,0.04090909090909091,12,0.05454545454545454,13,0.05909090909090909,4,0.01818181818181818,19,0.08636363636363636,1,0.004545454545454545,0,0.0,1,0.004545454545454545,0,0.0,0,5,0,5,0.022727272727272728,3,0.013636363636363636,0.9925
