17,How do I organize my closet?,baseline,"Hello! I'd be happy to help you organize your closet! Here are some steps you can follow to get started:

1. Take everything out: Start by taking everything out of your closet, including clothes, shoes, accessories, and storage containers. This will give you a clear view of what you have and help you decide what you can get rid of.
2. Sort and purge: Go through each item and sort it into three piles: keep, donate/sell, and discard. Be honest with yourself about what you really need and what you can let go of. Consider donating or selling items that are still in good condition but no longer fit or suit your style.
3. Categorize and group: Once you've purged your closet, group similar items together (e.g., tops, bottoms, dresses, outerwear, etc.). Within each group, sort items by type, color, and size.
4. Use storage containers: Use storage containers or bins to store items that you don't use frequently, such as out-of-season clothes or off-season accessories. Label each container so you can easily find what you need.
5. Utilize vertical space: Maximize your closet's vertical space by using stackable shelves or hanging rods with multiple levels. This will help you make the most of your closet's space.
6. Implement a ""one in, one out"" policy: To prevent clutter from building up again, adopt a ""one in, one out"" policy, where you get rid of an old item every time you bring a new one into your closet.
7. Keep shoes in order: Store your shoes in a designated area, such as on a shoe rack or in a shoe organizer. This will help keep them from getting scattered throughout your closet.
8. Hang clothes by type: Hang clothes by type, such as dresses, tops, and pants. This will make it easier to find what you're looking for and keep your closet organized.
9. Use dividers: Use dividers to separate different categories of clothes within your closet. This will help you find what you need quickly and easily.
10. Keep your closet tidy: Set aside some time each week to maintain your closet's organization. Hang up clothes that are wrinkled or out of place, and put away items that are not being used.

I hope these tips help you get started on organizing your closet! Remember, it's important to purge items that are no longer needed or useful, and to keep your closet tidy to ensure that it remains organized and functional.",411,0,4,0.009732360097323601,6,0.014598540145985401,2,0.004866180048661801,0,0.0,1,0.0024330900243309003,1,0.0024330900243309003,14,0.0340632603406326,1,0.0024330900243309003,24,0.058394160583941604,15,0.0364963503649635,0,0.0,25,0.06082725060827251,0,0.0,0,0.0,0,0.0,4,0.009732360097323601,1,0,0,1,0.0024330900243309003,0,0.0,0.994
